In [22]: 
def replace_word(dataframe):
    dataframe['Item_Fat_Content']=dataframe['Item_Fat_Content'].str.replace('LF','Low_Fat')
    dataframe['Item_Fat_Content']=dataframe['Item_Fat_Content'].str.replace('Low Fat','Low_Fat')
    dataframe['Item_Fat_Content']=dataframe['Item_Fat_Content'].str.replace('low fat','Low_Fat')
    dataframe['Item_Fat_Content']=dataframe['Item_Fat_Content'].str.replace('Regular','Regular_Fat')
    dataframe['Item_Fat_Content']=dataframe['Item_Fat_Content'].str.replace('reg','Regular_Fat')
    return dataframe

Handling null values

In [29]: 
def handle_null(dataframe, num_column, obj_column):
    for i in dataframe[num_column]:
        dataframe[i]=dataframe[i].fillna(dataframe[i].median())
        
    for i in dataframe[obj_column]:
        dataframe[i]=dataframe[i].fillna(dataframe[i].mode()[0])    
        
    return dataframe

Handling outliers

In [33]: 
Q3_item_vis=np.percentile(x["Item_Visibility"], 75)
Q1_item_vis=np.percentile(x["Item_Visibility"], 25)

Q3_Item_MRP=np.percentile(x["Item_MRP"], 75)
Q1_Item_MRP=np.percentile(x["Item_MRP"], 25)
In [34]: 
def outlier_handle(dataframe):

    IQR_item_vis=Q3_item_vis-Q1_item_vis
    UB_item_vis=Q3_item_vis+(1.5*IQR_item_vis)
    LB_item_vis=Q1_item_vis-(1.5*IQR_item_vis)
    dataframe["Item_Visibility"]=dataframe["Item_Visibility"].apply(lambda x:UB_item_vis if x>UB_item_vis else x)
    dataframe["Item_Visibility"]=dataframe["Item_Visibility"].apply(lambda y:LB_item_vis if y<LB_item_vis else y)
    
    
        
    IQR_Item_MRP=Q3_Item_MRP-Q1_Item_MRP
    UB_Item_MRP=Q3_Item_MRP+(1.5*IQR_Item_MRP)
    LB_Item_MRP=Q1_Item_MRP-(1.5*IQR_Item_MRP)
    dataframe["Item_MRP"]=dataframe["Item_MRP"].apply(lambda x:UB_Item_MRP if x>UB_Item_MRP else x)
    dataframe["Item_MRP"]=dataframe["Item_MRP"].apply(lambda y:LB_Item_MRP if y<LB_Item_MRP else y)

    
    return dataframe

def encode_categorical_feature(dataframe, obj_column):
    for i in obj_column:
        dataframe[i]=encoder.fit_transform(dataframe[i])
        
    return dataframe

Data Scaling ¶
In [51]: 
def scale_data(x):
    scale.fit(x)
    x_scaled=scale.transform(x)

    x=pd.DataFrame(data=x_scaled, columns=x.columns)
    
    return x

Model Training and Evaluations of models ¶

In [55]: 
def model_evaluate(y_test,y_pred):
    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)
    mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
    r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)
    print('MAE is {}'.format(round(mae, 3)))
    print('MSE is {}'.format(round(mse, 3)))
    print('R2 score is {}'.format(round(r2, 3)))

Creating dataframe with MAE, MSE and R2-Score of all trained models to better visualization ¶
In [67]: 
regressors = {
    'Linear Regression' : lr,
    'Decision Tree' : DT,
    'Random Forest' : RF,
    'K-nearest Neighbors' : KNN,
    'Gradient Boost' : GB
}
results=pd.DataFrame(columns=['Train Score', 'Test Score', 'MAE', 'MSE', 'R2-score'])
for method,func in regressors.items():
    pred = func.predict(x_test)
    results.loc[method]= [
                          func.score(x_train, y_train),
                          func.score(x_test, y_test),
                          np.round(mean_absolute_error(y_test,pred),3),
                          np.round(mean_squared_error(y_test,pred),3),
                          np.round(r2_score(y_test,pred),3)
                         ]
    
final_result=results.sort_values('R2-score',ascending=False).style.background_gradient(cmap='Greens',subset=['R2-score'])    
display(final_result)
